\begin_layout Standard
The 
\family typewriter
GPlotFun
\family default
 package is a collection of gretl scripts and functions for advanced plotting
 methods.
 Gretl's built-in plotting facility makes heavy use of the well-known open-sourc
e graphing utility 
\emph on
Gnuplot
\emph default
 (URL: 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "http://www.gnuplot.info/"
target "http://www.gnuplot.info/"
literal "false"

\end_inset

).
 Gretl already offers a plotting facility, as described in Ch.
 8 in the manual.
 However, some types of plots are either hard to realize using the current
 state or not supported at all.
 This package is an attempt to bridge the gap between Gretl's current state
 of employing gnuplot and gnuplot's huge capability to draw very different
 and advanced plots.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\family typewriter
GPlotFun
\family default
 package makes heavily use of gretl's support of bundles which offer a highly
 flexible way of programming.
 This initial package version is a suggestion, and the author is looking
 forward to collaborate with interested people to continue its development.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 
\family typewriter
GPlotFun
\family default
 package comprises the following features:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Time-series plots with vertical and horizontal lines, with vertical and
 horizontal shaded areas, and impulse as well as point plots.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Scatter plots supporting classes of points and lines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stacked barplots combined with line plots.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Heatmaps
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Frequency plot
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Many parameters can be controlled for obtaining high-quality graphs.
\end_layout

